We first extract the necessary information.

1. Debt to Equity Ratio 
 • Liabilities (from balance sheet End data): Only Taxes Payable is non‐zero = 727140.68  
 • Owner's Equity (End): 28405999.64  
  Debt to Equity Ratio = Liabilities / Owner’s Equity = 727140.68 / 28405999.64 ≈ 0.0256  
  Rounded to two decimals, this is approximately 0.03.

2. Net Profit Margin 
 • Net Profit (from income statement): 405999.64  
 • Total Revenue: 14542813.42  
  Net Profit Margin = (Net Profit / Total Revenue) × 100  
  = (405999.64 / 14542813.42) × 100 ≈ 2.79%  

3. Return on Assets (ROA) 
 • Total Assets (balance sheet End): 29133140.32  
 • ROA = (Net Profit / Total Assets) × 100  
  = (405999.64 / 29133140.32) × 100 ≈ 1.39%

4. Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio 
 • Net Sales (using Main Business Revenue from income statement): 14542813.42  
 • Accounts Receivable: At beginning = 0 (from 2023-12-31) and End = 10221447.35  
  Average Accounts Receivable = (0 + 10221447.35) / 2 = 5110723.675  
  Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio = Net Sales / Average Accounts Receivable  
  ≈ 14542813.42 / 5110723.675 ≈ 2.85

Thus, the final results are:

{
  "solution": {
    "Debt to Equity Ratio": "0.03",
    "Net Profit Margin": "2.79%",
    "Return on Assets (ROA)": "1.39%",
    "Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio": "2.85"
  }
}
